            <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
            <p>Welcome to PixelPulse! This Privacy Policy ("Policy") explains how University of London and ASP Team 54 ("We," "Us," or "Our") collects, uses, shares, and protects your personal information when you use the PixelPulse application (the "Service"). By using the Service, you consent to the practices described in this Policy. Please read this Policy carefully to understand how we handle your personal information.</p>

            <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
            <p>2.1 Information You Provide: We collect information you voluntarily provide when you use the Service, such as when you register an account, post coding projects, interact with other users, or contact our support team. This information may include your name, email address, profile picture, and other personal details.
                <br><br>
                2.2 Automatically Collected Information: We may collect certain information automatically when you use the Service. This information may include your IP address, device type, operating system, browser type, and other technical information. We may also collect information about your usage patterns, interactions with content, and preferences.
                <br><br>
                2.3 Cookies and Similar Technologies: We use cookies, web beacons, and similar tracking technologies to collect information about your browsing behavior and preferences. You can manage your cookie preferences through your browser settings.
            </p>

            <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
            <p>3.1 Providing and Improving the Service: We use your information to provide, maintain, and improve the Service. This includes personalizing your experience, developing new features, and analyzing usage patterns to enhance our platform.
                <br><br>
                3.2 Communication: We may use your contact information to send you service-related communications, updates, and notifications. You can opt-out of certain communications in your account settings.
                <br><br>
                3.3 Research and Analytics: We may use your information for research and analytics purposes to better understand user behavior, trends, and preferences. This helps us improve our Service and develop new features.
                <br><br>
                3.4 Legal Compliance: We may use your information to comply with legal obligations, respond to legal requests, or protect our rights, privacy, safety, or property, as well as that of our users and the public.
            </p>

            <h2>4. How We Share Your Information</h2>
            <p>4.1 With Other Users: Some of your information, such as your username and profile picture, may be visible to other users of the Service as part of your public profile. Be cautious about sharing sensitive personal information on your public profile.
                <br><br>
                4.2 Third-Party Service Providers: We may share your information with third-party service providers who help us operate, maintain, and improve the Service. These providers are contractually obligated to protect your information.
                <br><br>
                4.3 Legal Requirements: We may disclose your information in response to a legal request, such as a court order or government inquiry, or to enforce our Terms of Service and other policies.
                <br><br>
                4.4 Business Transfers: If we are involved in a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or a portion of our assets, your information may be transferred as part of the transaction.
            </p>

            <h2>5. Your Privacy Choices</h2>
            <p>5.1 Account Settings: You can review and update your account settings to control what information is visible to other users and manage communication preferences.
                <br><br>
                5.2 Cookies: You can manage your cookie preferences through your browser settings.
                <br><br>
                5.3 Access and Deletion: You may request access to the personal information we hold about you or request its deletion by contacting us on Slack. We will respond to your request as required by applicable law.
            </p>

            <h2>6. Data Security</h2>
            <p>We implement reasonable security measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, and destruction. However, no online platform can guarantee absolute security, so please use caution when sharing personal information online.</p>

            <h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
            <p>The Service is not intended for individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect or solicit personal information from children. If you believe that we have inadvertently collected information from a child, please contact us, and we will take appropriate steps to delete the information.</p>

            <h2>8. Changes to this Policy</h2>
            <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. We will notify you of any material changes by posting the updated Policy on the Service. We encourage you to review this Policy periodically.</p>

            <h2>9. Contact Us</h2>
            <p>If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or your personal information, please contact us on Slack.
                <br><br>
                Thank you for using PixelPulse, and we are committed to protecting your privacy!
            </p>

